  "base_path": "/nominate-someone-to-collect-state-pension",
  "content_id": "be13f64e-336f-4580-b03a-45b1aa3e31f9",
  "description": "Find out how to nominate someone to collect your State Pension for you",
  "details": {
    "body": "\n<div class=\"summary\">\n<p>Contact your account provider to nominate someone to collect your State Pension.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Most banks, building societies or other account providers allow a third party access to your account, eg with a second card.</p>\n\n<p>Contact your bank, building society or other account provider for more information.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"lasting-power-of-attorney\">Lasting power of attorney</h2>\n\n<p>You can appoint one or more people to make decisions about money and property for you, including collecting your State Pension. This is known as making a <a href=\"/power-of-attorney\">lasting power of attorney (<abbr title=\"Lasting power of attorney\">LPA</abbr>)</a>.</p>\n\n<p>To make an <abbr title=\"Lasting power of attorney\">LPA</abbr>, you must be:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>over 18</li>\n  <li>able to make your own decisions (have ‘mental capacity’)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div role=\"note\" aria-label=\"Information\" class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>There’s a different process if you want to collect State Pension on behalf of <a href=\"/become-appointee-for-someone-claiming-benefits\">someone who can’t make their own decisions</a>.</p>\n</div>\n\n",
    "external_related_links": [

    ]
  },
